description:
This is a 9 minute workout called 'Lower Back Pain Relief Exercises for Pregnancy - Physio Guided Home Routine' from the channel Michelle Kenway.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Stretching and Cardio/Mat.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Reboot Workout and The Comfort Moves vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Physiotherapist guided lower back pain relief exercises for all stages of pregnancy. Relieve back muscle tightness and discomfort with these pregnancy exercises for your lower and middle back. Physio Michelle from https://www.pelvicexercises.com.au guides you through this gentle home exercise routine with no equipment required. 

Please note that these exercises are not appropriate for pregnant women with lower back disc injury.

This lower back home exercise routine for pregnancy consists of a series of gently lower and middle back spinal mobility exercises.This routine is performed kneeling on all fours and in side lying. The exercises are appropriate for all stages of pregnancy including the last trimester as they do not involve lying on the back, a position which should be avoided for pregnancy exercises from 16 weeks onwards. All the included exercises provide gentle movement for the muscles and joints of the middle and lower back.
